; cell-organ-layer.form - trusted cells form organs over layered substrate.
;
; THE ASK
;   Trusted cells can form organs that share content via channels and shared
;   substrate that can be layered.
;
; THE SHAPE
;   A cell is the smallest sovereign participant. An organ is a quorum of
;   trusted cells with a shared role. A channel is the consented path between
;   organs. A substrate layer is the content-addressed surface where receipts,
;   summaries, memories, predictions, reports, and research can stack without
;   becoming one undifferentiated stream.
;
;   This is the next composition:
;     cell -> trusted cell quorum -> organ -> channel -> substrate layer
;          -> higher layer -> shared mesh memory/action
;
; RUNNABLE HEART
;   form-stdlib/cell-organ-layer.fk names:
;     col-cell                id, role, trust, consent, vitality, offers
;     col-trusted?            trust + consent + vitality gate
;     col-organ               id, kind, cells, channels, layers
;     col-organ-forms?        quorum of trusted cells becomes an organ
;     col-layer               name, level, content-addressed, consented, receipt
;     col-content             kind, privacy, bytes, NodeID, receipt
;     col-organ-can-share?    formed organ + open channel + valid layer/content
;     col-layered-organ?      formed organ with enough valid substrate layers
;     col-layer-promote?      lower-layer content can become higher-layer memory
;
; LAYERS
;   The first substrate stack can be:
;     0 raw-local
;       Raw samples stay inside the cell/organ unless separately offered.
;
;     1 summary
;       Derived readings: temperature summary, motion state, light level,
;       hydration risk, air quality class, soil moisture band.
;
;     2 memory
;       Durable content-addressed observations and friend-cache receipts.
;
;     3 prediction
;       Sequence/pattern forecasts built from consented memories.
;
;     4 report
;       Human/organ-readable summaries with confidence, provenance, and limits.
;
;     5 research
;       Aggregated, de-identified, consent-scoped study material.
;
; ACTIVATION
;   The organ exists only while enough trusted cells are present. Sharing exists
;   only while a channel is open and content is safe for the target layer. Layer
;   promotion is explicit: a summary can become memory, memory can feed
;   prediction, prediction can feed report, and report can feed research only
;   with address, consent, and receipt intact.
;
; WHY THIS MATTERS
;   This gives the mesh a body plan. A sensor cell, nutrient cell, memory cell,
;   predictor cell, reporter cell, researcher cell, scout cell, caregiver cell,
;   sage cell, and power cell are no longer a loose swarm. They can become an
;   organ when trust and vitality are high enough, speak through channels, and
;   layer shared substrate content without losing sovereignty.
;
; PROOF
;   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk \
;     form-stdlib/hati-mesh.fk \
;     form-stdlib/cell-organ-layer.fk \
;     form-stdlib/tests/cell-organ-layer-band.fk
;
; KIN
;   mesh-seed.form, organism-mesh.form, mesh-cell-design.form, hati-mesh.form,
;   organ-offer.form, shared-sensing.form, sensor-organ-channel.form,
;   recognition-router.form, mesh-health.form.
